overview: The user initiated a comprehensive review of their sleep questionnaire
  application, requesting validation against the Statement of Work and detailed
  specifications. The agent conducted a thorough analysis of the codebase,
  identifying several critical gaps, such as missing detection for specific
  sleep disorders (e.g., COMISA), incomplete scoring for Excessive Daytime
  Sleepiness (EDS), and the absence of a tiredness severity scale with
  associated safety warnings. A detailed plan was then formulated, prioritizing
  these missing features. The agent proceeded to implement the first
  high-priority item, integrating a 1-10 tiredness severity scale into the
  questionnaire. This involved modifying data models, validation schemas, and UI
  components to capture the severity, display a user-friendly slider, and
  present an urgent safety warning within the questionnaire and the generated
  PDF report if the user-reported tiredness severity was high.
